5 Blue-tailed Bee-eaters flying over deck 5 minutes past 6 in the evening. Flying towards SW. I saw them over deck 5 minutes later and they were flying around and now I suspected that they were looking for a place to sleep.

30 minutes later they are sitting on the rail and I manage to get a few pictures. Of course dark so the quality is poor.

They make a lot of noise, 30 meters away and I try to make a recording with a lot of wind noise as I try to avoid the sound from the engine behind me
